Nigeria’s opponent and host for Friday’s 2022 World Cup qualifying playoff, the Black Stars of Ghana, have arrived Kumasi, venue of the first leg match. The Black Stars host the Super Eagles in the first leg at the Baba Yara Sports Stadium in Kumasi on Friday March 25, 2022 before traveling to Abuja for the second leg on March 29, 2022.The team arrived in Kumasi on Tuesday afternoon and were met by fans and journalist. Debutants Denis Odoi (Club Brugge), Montari Kamaheni (Ashdod), Elisha Owusu (Gent) and Dennis Korsah (Hearts of Oak) have arrived in camp. The team will train today at the Baba Yara Sports Stadium. Crystal Palace forward Jordan Ayew has been cleared to travel after testing negative for COVID-19. According to the Ghana FA Communications Director, Jordan Ayew will join the team on Wednesday. Ghana will be hoping to secure a ticket to the World Cup to be staged in Qatar in November this year.